{"id": "1375876741674963095", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "328095417436864512", "author_name": "fatewriter", "content": "For pvp, the gacha part is literally only need to have a single copy of a character or wheel to have it unlocked and work as intended.\nAs i said before half the \"skill\" is in deck building, if you don't have something you can try to change your tactics and deck composition, the other half is card counting and predicting the enemy plays and win conditions.\nAs someone who haven't spent a dime in this game(cuz i literally can't pay with irl money in this game due to technical issues) it's not as bad as you make it.\nCompared to other card games i would say the paywall isn't high.\nIf you want, you can post your characters and wheels here and let people help you out in creating a deck, also we can give you tips and some strategies stuff", "timestamp": "2025-05-24T16:42:57.769000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-05-24T16:44:03.690000+00:00"}
{"id": "1375880473321930863", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "91654723089760256", "author_name": "tallythetalarin", "content": "It doesn't matter if it's a single copy or duped tho\n\nYou cannot get most of these characters whenever you want, only on very specific banners, and this also goes for the standard non-limited chars.\n\nOther card games, at least Hearthstone, typically has a mode where all p2w is disabled by default. It's also the main component of the game, not a supplementary to a PvE focus.\n\nLike for example I have been trying to do Erica taunt-reinforce with Fouette, but today all of my matches the taunt card is somewhere in the last 3 cards of my draw pile, lol.\n\nI suppose asking for help is my last resort but I appreciate it. If it doesn't go well, I'll just stick to Dtide.", "timestamp": "2025-05-24T16:57:47.463000+00:00"}
