{"id": "1375880763291074721", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "91654723089760256", "author_name": "tallythetalarin", "content": "This is all I have, +the event wheels for Corpo, 24, Ghelot", "timestamp": "2025-05-24T16:58:56.597000+00:00"}
{"id": "1375892768966049803", "channel_id": "1326453691527594035", "author_id": "328095417436864512", "author_name": "fatewriter", "content": "You can go for the easy to use frenzy lotan comp\nWhich has lotan, doll, nautila, ogier/aigis\nAs for wheels you use frenzy, the bullet looking wheel, noble staff and the last one any support/defensive wheel.\nThe win condition is to get lotan equip with frenzy and have some strikes in hand(you can first equip the bullet looking wheel to her to have extra stikes in the deck and then equip frenzy)this would allow lotan to generate 100 alimus every 3 stikes used, so you tear down the enemy through strikes, doll is there mostly for her dispel skill, noble staff to cleanse any debuff inflicted upon lotan.\nOfc you might need to change strategies depending on the enemy.\n\nAnother team you can try is paralysis team which is quite popular, can't give you much on this type of comp since i don't have tulu, but you can try\nTulu, ramona, any healer or red, erica.\n\nYou can also try\nAurita, doll, goliath, aigis\nAurita with dream of the sea\nA defensive or support wheel for doll\nThe remove enemy buff wheel for goliath\nA defensive wheel for aigis\nThis comp probably need some fine tuning and due to goliath and aurita they need more thinking on what order to play cards and how enemy will play(especially careful since they will try to snipe aurita or doll)", "timestamp": "2025-05-24T17:46:38.973000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-05-24T17:47:01.455000+00:00"}
